# {{Name}}

A JWT-authenticated full-stack MVP scaffolded by `mvp new dotnet-angular-jwt-mvp`.

## Layout

- `backend/` — .NET 9 clean-architecture solution with JWT auth, MediatR/CQS, FluentValidation, EF Core.
- `frontend/` — Angular workspace with `api`, `components`, and `domain` libraries plus the main app.
- `frontend/e2e/` — Playwright tests using the page-object model.

## Getting started

### Backend

```
cd backend
dotnet build
dotnet run --project src/{{Name}}.Api
```

The API listens on http://localhost:5000 by default and uses an in-memory database. To target SQL Server, set `ConnectionStrings:Default` in `src/{{Name}}.Api/appsettings.json`.

**Important:** replace `Jwt:SigningKey` in `appsettings.json` before running outside development.

### Frontend

```
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
```

Then browse to http://localhost:4200.

### End-to-end tests

```
cd frontend
npx playwright install
npx playwright test
```
